- .woff or .woff2 (recommended for web)
- Optional: .ttf, .eot, .svg (older formats)

Letâ€™s say you have a font named MyFont.woff2.

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Upload the Font to Your Theme
1) Go to your Shopify admin â†’ Online Store â†’ Themes.
2) Click Actions â†’ Edit Code on your live (or draft) theme.
3) In the left sidebar, scroll down to Assets, then click â€œAdd a new assetâ€.
4) Upload your MyFont.woff2 (or any other font file).

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Add @font-face in CSS
1) In the Assets folder, open base.css (or theme.css, styles.css, etc.).
2) Add the following code at the top:

@font-face {
  font-family: 'MyFont';
  src: url('{{ 'MyFont.woff2' | asset_url }}') format('woff2');
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
}


ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Apply the Font in CSS
body {
  font-family: 'MyFont', sans-serif;
}

h1, h2, h3 {
  font-family: 'MyFont', serif;
}




ğŸ§  Optional: Add Font Setting in settings_schema.json
To allow merchants to select the font from the Theme Editor:

{
  "type": "font_picker",
  "id": "custom_font",
  "label": "Choose custom font"
}

Then in your CSS file:

body {
  font-family: {{ settings.custom_font.family }}, sans-serif;
}

But this only works for Google Fonts or fonts available in Shopify's font library â€” not for uploaded fonts.

